{
  "texts": [
    "Subsequently, we freeze the remaining model parameters and train using keyframe-text pairs from the ChronoMagic dataset.",
    "Since this phase does not involve temporal changes, the model can learn these static features more accurately and also alleviate the impact of video watermarks.",
    "In the second phase, we reintroduce the pre-trained temporal layer and propose integrating MagicAdapter-T into the temporal layer.",
    "We then freeze other parameters and train using video-text pairs from the ChronoMagic dataset.",
    "Since spatial features have been learned in the previous phase, the optimization during the temporal training phase can focus more on the F outs (X) = F sap (X) + α × R ada (F sap (X)),(8)F outt (Y) = F temp (Y) + β × M ada (Y),(9)where F outs ∈ R B×C×1×H×W and F outt ∈ R B×C×F×H×W, α and β are scaling coefficients, B, C, F, H, and W represent the batch size, channel, frame number, height, and width."
  ]
}